'''Technomad''' is a term coined by [[Steven K. Roberts]] (amateur radio [[Callsign (radio)|call sign]]: N4RVE) to describe a nomadic person who remains connected through communications media, during travel, exploration, and online nomadic living.

==Early days of the Term==
As the father of the term, Steve Roberts began with creation of the "[[Behemoth (vehicle)|Behemoth]]", a human-powered vehicle, equipped with [[amateur radio]] communications gear.  This pioneering work has inspired many others to choose online nomadic living. sup.

==The term in Present Day==
Later, Roberts created yet another more advanced online vehicle, the "[[Microship]]".

